<P>
CSUN STUDIES REPORT ON CAMPUS ARENA 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Cal State Northridge might announce as early as Friday the results of a 
feasibility study on an on-campus, indoor sports arena. 
</P>
<P>
The report could result in a cooperative venture between the school and the 
Ogden Corp., a New York-based conglomerate that has been gathering data on the 
proposed facility for more than a month. 
</P>
<P>
Jane Kato, executive assistant to Elliott Mininberg, a CSUN vice president, 
said Tuesday that the school had received a detailed report from Ogden on 
Monday and might respond publicly to its findings by the end of the week. 
</P>
