THE STATE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The South Lake Tahoe City Council has voted to replace former council member 
and mayor Terry Trupp by appointment, rather than by a special election. Trupp, 
who resigned July 31 after his arrest on cocaine trafficking and money 
laundering charges, is being held without bail in Sacramento County Jail. City 
Council members agreed to accept applications from people interested in the 
position until 5 p.m. July 28. All applicants will be interviewed and the 
original list will be trimmed to a group of finalists, from which the successor 
will be appointed. Trupp's council term runs through June of next year. His 
tenure as mayor automatically expired at the end of last month. Trupp, 46, was 
among about 20 people arrested after a 20-month investigation by federal, state 
and local agents called "Operation Deep Snow." 
</P>
