<HEADLINE>
<P>
NUCLEAR PLANT SHUT DOWN 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From United Press International 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
PLYMOUTH, Mass. 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The Pilgrim nuclear power plant was shut down manually Tuesday because the 
facility suffered an unexplained loss of vacuum in its main condenser, 
officials said. The condenser is on the steam side of the plant and did not 
cause any radiation leak, a spokesman said. 
</P>
