<HEADLINE>
<P>
METRO DIGEST / LOCAL NEWS IN BRIEF: BALDWIN PARK ACTS TO LIMIT SMOKING 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The Baldwin Park City Council has introduced an ordinance that would ban 
smoking in public areas of city buildings such as the council chamber, the City 
Hall lobby, restrooms and hallways. 
</P>
<P>
The proposed ordinance is similar to smoking bans adopted in Alhambra, Duarte, 
Pasadena and Los Angeles. 
</P>
<P>
But unlike ordinances in other communities, the plan introduced by the council 
last week would not regulate smoking in restaurants and other private 
businesses. 
</P>
<P>
The proposed ban would expand the number of places where smoking restrictions 
are in force. 
</P>
