<HEADLINE>
<P>
MAN HIT ON HEAD DURING POSSIBLE ROBBERY DIES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
An elderly San Diego man who was struck in the head Sunday, during what police 
say may have been a robbery attempt, died Tuesday, authorities said. 
</P>
<P>
Louis Ladd, 77, of the 2500 block Commercial Street was pronounced dead at 2:10 
p.m. at UC San Diego Medical Center, said Deputy Coroner George Dickason. 
</P>
<P>
An autopsy was scheduled for today. 
</P>
<P>
Ladd was struck during a struggle at his home Sunday, said police spokesman 
Bill Robinson. 
</P>
<P>
Information on the incident was sketchy and police asked witnesses to call 
235-TIPS. 
</P>
