<HEADLINE>
<P>
NEWSWIRE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Alan Eagleson, executive director of the NHL Players Assn., has postponed a 
union meeting that was scheduled to review measures that would diminish his 
power. 
</P>
<P>
Player representatives from the 21 clubs were supposed to meet in Toronto next 
Monday and Tuesday to ratify measures adopted after Eagleson survived a 
no-confidence vote last month. 
</P>
<P>
Eagleson said he canceled the meeting because an audit, which was requested 
after Eagleson acknowledged using money belonging to the association for loans 
to friends, isn't ready. 
</P>
</TEXT>
