<HEADLINE>
<P>
BRIEFLY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
AT&amp;T Introduces New PCs: American Telephone &amp; Telegraph Co. unveiled 
four personal computers made to AT&amp;T specifications by Intel Corp., which 
is substantially replacing Italy's Ing. C. Olivetti &amp; Co. as the company's 
PC supplier. The computers are specially designed to be used in networks and 
can be purchased with software that allows them to perform particular 
networking or communications jobs. They range in price from $2,995 to $22,225. 
The announcement was expected after AT&amp;T's announcement last week of a 
personal computer development agreement with Intel, which is better known for 
selling bare chips, not whole computers. 
