<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY DIGEST / LOCAL NEWS IN BRIEF: BREA; 
</P>
<P>
COMMISSION VOTES TO EXPAND LANDFILL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The Orange County Planning Commission on Tuesday voted 4 to 1 to recommend an 
expansion of the Olinda Canyon landfill, which is scheduled to be at capacity 
in 1994. 
</P>
<P>
The commission did not follow the recommendation of the County Waste Management 
Commission, which last week recommended that further studies be conducted on 
potential landfill sites in Gypsum Canyon and West Fremont Canyon, in addition 
to Olinda. The planning commissioners said the Board of Supervisors should 
decide which landfill site should receive further study. 
</P>
<P>
Supervisors are scheduled to consider a location for a landfill in North Orange 
County at an Aug. 16 meeting. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Column; Brief 
</P>
