<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY DIGEST / LOCAL NEWS IN BRIEF: FULLERTON; 
</P>
<P>
15-YEAR-OLD ARRESTED IN DEATH OF MOTEL OWNER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A 15-year-old Fullerton youth has been arrested in connection with the death of 
a Diamond Bar woman who was co-owner of a Fullerton motel where the youth 
lived, police said Tuesday. 
</P>
<P>
The youth, whose name was not released because he is a juvenile, was arrested 
on suspicion of murder, rape, robbery and burglary. 
</P>
<P>
The body of the victim, Pravina Dholakia, 40, was found by a janitor in a suite 
next to the lobby of the Willow Tree Motel at 1015 Harbor Blvd., Police Lt. Ron 
Rowell said. Police had not confirmed the time of death. 
</P>
<P>
An autopsy Tuesday determined that Dholakia died of strangulation, police said. 
</P>
<P>
The youth is being held at Orange County Juvenile Hall. 
</P>
</TEXT>
