<P>
KITCHELL CONTRACTORS OF IRVINE NAMES JAMES W. HOWARD AS NEW PRESIDENT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
Compiled by Michael Flagg, Times staff writer 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
James W. Howard, vice president of Kitchell Development Co., was named 
president of Kitchell Contractors in Irvine. 
</P>
<P>
He succeeds Greg Denk, who was promoted to executive vice president and chief 
operating officer of Kitchell Corp., the contractor's parent company in 
Phoenix. 
</P>
<P>
Denk is credited with taking Kitchell Contractors' California revenue from $30 
million in 1980 to the more than $120 million projected for 1989. That makes it 
one of the county's five largest contractors, according to the company. 
</P>
<P>
Howard, employed at Kitchell since 1980, will oversee such construction 
projects as Irvine City Hall, Western Digital's new headquarters in Irvine and 
Fiesta Marketplace in Santa Ana. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Brief; Column 
</P>
