<HEADLINE>
<P>
BRIEFLY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Aeroflot Seeks to Join IATA: The Soviet airline Aeroflot applied to join the 
187-member International Air Transportation Assn., IATA said. IATA spokesman 
John Brindley said acceptance was a formality and Aeroflot, the largest 
non-IATA airline in the world, should become a member within two or three 
weeks. He said it was not likely to affect Aeroflot fares, since IATA fare 
decisions are not binding, but it was likely to help bring Aeroflot procedures 
and documentation into line with international practice. Airlines also can 
exchange information quickly through IATA in the event of a hijacking or bomb 
threat. 
</P>
</TEXT>
