<P>
BODY FOUND IN LOPEZ CANYON AREA 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times staff and wire service reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The Los Angeles County Sheriff's Department is investigating the death of a 
woman who was found shot to death this morning on a street in the Lopez Canyon 
area, authorities said. 
</P>
<P>
The body of the unidentified woman was found by a Los Angeles police officer on 
patrol at 3:36 a.m. in the 12300 block of Paxton Avenue, Sgt. Bryan Williams 
said. 
</P>
<P>
That part of Paxton Avenue is in a small unincorporated area between Lake View 
Terrace and Pacoima, and Los Angeles police officers routinely use the street 
when driving between the two areas. 
</P>
<P>
Williams said detectives have not determined a motive for the shooting and have 
no suspects. 
