<TEXT>
<P>
The Senate voted today to name a grassy plot near the Chinese Embassy in 
Washington "Tian An Men Square Park" in honor of pro-democracy demonstrators in 
Beijing. 
</P>
<P>
In addition to memorializing demonstrators who were killed by the Chinese army, 
said Sen. Malcolm Wallop (R-Wyo.), who sponsored the legislation, the action 
serves "to remind Beijing that America will never and can never forget the 
ruthlessness and callousness of the Chinese government in crushing their 
citizen-demonstrators and their aspirations." The amendment was added by voice 
vote to a bill authorizing State Department programs for the new budget year. 
</P>
