<TEXT>
<P>
A judge sentenced the mother of a junior high school student to 10 days in 
Baltimore's "dirty, funky, stinky " jail for allowing her daughter to miss 101 
days of school last year. 
</P>
<P>
After sentencing Debra Shaw to the maximum jail time Tuesday, District Judge 
David W. Young then instructed a jailer to give the woman's two children a tour 
of the courthouse holding cells. 
</P>
<P>
"Your mother is going to the dirty, funky, stinky Baltimore City Jail because 
the two of you have played hooky," Young said. 
</P>
<P>
Young blamed their mother's laziness for the children's truancy, noting that 
she had failed to show up for several meetings with school officials before 
charges were filed. 
